SSyynnooppssiiss
       #include <lber.h> #include <ldap.h>

       int ldap_unbind(LDAP *ld);

       int ldap_unbind_s(LDAP *ld);

DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       ldap_unbind  is  used to unbind from the directory, termi-
       nate the current association, and free the resources  con-
       tained in the ld structure. Once it is called, the connec-
       tion to the LDAP server is closed, and the ld structure is
       invalid.   ldap_unbind_s   is   just   another   name  for
       ldap_unbind; both of these functions are synchronous.

